translated: Kogge, Fritiof Olof, civil engineer, Gothenburg, born on September 1, 1897 in Kalvsund, Gothenburg and Bohus. 1st marriage to Nancy Burkitt. Children: Bodil Hildegard born in 1928, Gunvor Eliisiabeth in 1930, Nanette Isaibellla in 1942, and Birian Fritiof in 1944. — Studied at Gothenburg Upper Secondary School and graduated from Chalmers University of Technology. Owner of the engineering firm Fritiof Kogge and Knut And. Larsson's Electrical Company. Member of the city planning committee, hospital board, primary school board, vocational school board, and inspector for the vocational guidance in Råda municipality. Chairman of the board for Gothenburg Technical Institute and Gothenburg Morning Post in 1940-1941. Member of the Freemasons and Odd Fellows.
